{"ts": "2026-06-10T03:48:53.567Z", "event": "segment_end", "segment_id": 1, "start_ms": 1781063333567, "end_ms": 1781063341567, "text": "The prefill phase is generally compute-bound. You're doing a large matrix multiplication over all input tokens in parallel. On modern hardware that's fast, but the cost scales linearly with the number of input tokens. So if your system prompt is long, or your context window is large, prefill latency goes up proportionally."}
